PTR Pointer of random file PTRIn the DOS this function and statement allows the manipulation of the pointers in sequential files. Its form is:PTR<factor>where <factor> is the file's handle found using `FIN or `FOUT, and it may appear on the left hand side of an equal sign or in an expression. In the COS PTR will cause an error. Examples:A=FIN"FRED"PRINT PTR AOPTRA=PTRA+23